# Mudflat Skiff Landing — Illustration Prompt

Create a richly detailed, roughly square digital painting sized to sit beside narrative text on desktop or mobile screens. Depict a grounded late-medieval harbor campaign setting at low water with mud, piles, skiffs, tackle crates, and slimy harbor edges. Emphasize crisp readability, brighter maritime color accents, and clear spatial separation more than muddy painterly atmosphere.

- Composition: low-water landing below the dignity of the main quay, with a visible climb or route back up.
- Key elements: shallow skiffs, hook tackle, muddy piles, wet rope, and rough low-tide work.
- Character focus: the sort of practical harbor men who clearly know what was done wrong and still do not consider it their fault.
- Navigation hint: keep the return path toward Launch Quay visually plain.

